definitions: a person, country, or company that sends goods or services to another country for sale

examples.text: Brazil is the world's largest producer and exporter of sugar
a major oil exporter to the United States

shortDefinitions: person, country or company that sends goods or services to another country for sale

definitions: a person or group spreading or introducing ideas and beliefs to another country

examples.text: charges have been leveled against the West since its ascension as an exporter of ideas
Japan has only begun to be an exporter of culture in the last couple of decades

shortDefinitions: person or group spreading or introducing ideas and beliefs to another country
